					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7999577#post-4023345</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7999577/scp-4029#post-4023345</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 13 Oct 2018 22:36:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DarkStuff</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1581620</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>And thanks to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/maliceaforethought" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2902864&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1545372009" alt="MaliceAforethought" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2902864)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/maliceaforethought" >MaliceAforethought</a></span> for giving me the chance to work with him on something this crazy and cool, and also for making <span style="background:black; color:black">█████</span> Industrial in the first place. This GoI is damn fun to write. Batshit crazy, internally consistent (if not, then we might go around and make some edits), and just crazy fun. Thanks, British bro~! &lt;3</p> <p>Anyways, some things, like, about things. Firstly, as <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/meserach" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1507289&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1545372009" alt="Meserach" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1507289)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/meserach" >Meserach</a></span> pointed out&#8230; the word &quot;meme&quot; wasn't coined at the in-universe time of writing of this article. And thus, &quot;memetic&quot; and &quot;antimemetic&quot; might not have been used either. But, like, the other option is to make that distinction a <em>thing</em>. Footnotes specifying enough that someone knows &quot;oh it's memetic&quot;, or explaining all of how it works in the article (so that you go &quot;oh it's memetic&quot;). So, we opted to just&#8230; keep it as is for now, unless someone has a really good suggestion. Just didn't feel like it contributed to the article.</p> <p>This article currently links back to every existing <span style="background:black; color:black">█████</span> Industrial article on the site, and future installments might also be crosslinked at relevant points in this article. This is supposed to sort of act as a launchpad for articles that Malice and I want to write in the future. Oh, and Agent LaFerrier. Might be involved. Heheheh. Enjoy!</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Oh,&nbsp;also&nbsp;I&nbsp;made&nbsp;a&nbsp;drawing.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Yeh&nbsp;lookatit.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"><img src="http://www.scp-wiki.net/local--files/scp-4029/artyart" alt="artyart" class="image" /></div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
